.SH "Resources"
.VL 3m
.LI "\*L*auditMaxMemoryPages\*O"
This resource specifies the maximum number of 256-Kilobyte pages that are
allocated by \*LXIsso\*O when receiving report data from the \*Laudit_tool\*O
command.
Once
this threshold is reached, \*LXIsso\*O discards the oldest data page to make
room for new data.  The default value is 20.  This means that up to 5 Megabytes
of report data is accessible at any one time while viewing a report.
If the Brief Report mode is selected, less data is available since \*LXIsso\*O
stores both the brief and the full records to expand brief
format into long format.
This memory is freed after each report is finished,
so it is not a cumulative amount.
.LE
